Todays reading was centered around understanding what Kali and metasploit is, kali is a linux based tool
that was developed primarily for pentesting and security tools built in which can be used to research and 
reverse engineer programs. Kali was released in 2013 and like its predecessor backtrack remains free with 
an open-source, this version has been slimmed down from the backtrack version manning the program and the 
tools within in kali more efficient and relevant to offensive security.  

Metasploit is framework for pen-testing, it was originally released in 2003 and is used to simplify the hacking
process by automating some of the more repetitive tasks that are involved. Metasploit integrates with most other
hacking tools such as nmap and Nessus making it a go to tool in the industry.
